author: Reuters
title: DIARY - Today in Washington - July 8
text:
ALL TIMES IN EDT/GMT
0700/1100: The USDA issues weekly world rice price.
1000/1400: The USDA issues May Livestock and Meat Trade.
1030/1430: The Energy Information Administration issues weekly petroleum stocks and output data.
No set time: The Association of American Railroads issues Weekly Traffic of Major Railroads.
1300/1700: The Treasury Dept. sells 10-year notes.
1400/1800: The Federal Open Market Committee issues minutes from its meeting of June 17-18.
1500/1900: The Federal Reserve issues Consumer Installment Credit for May.
